People who survive their appointed deaths are the same. They are soulless things that breathe, eat, and shit, but are no longer alive. Their existences become a series of events that they observe as outsiders. They are no longer part of the world.

I am speaking, of course, about the soul. I believe the soul is a real thing. The body is nothing more than a vessel for the soul. When the allotted time for the vessel expires, the soul departed and leaves behind an empty shell.
They fell outside of God's cruel design and continued to exist in a world where they were no longer needed.

The moment when a person survived their appointed death, life ended despite their continued existence. Instead of dying from an illness, or by murder, or by accident, or by suicide, their heart continued to beat but their life was over.

Are you sometimes curious to know if people are meant to die at a certain time? I'm not talking about the idea of predestination, but the idea that we all have an appointed death, a time when our lives are supposed to end.
